<br>
I mean, which would you rather have?<br>
<br>
AC5, +30 hp, +30 mana<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
+36 mana<br>
<br>
On raising the points you get at the outset, no, I don't feel that's necessary.  Raising the INT and WIS caps is simply a bone they're throwing casters to raise their mana pools slightly.  At level 60, the 55 INT you can get over 200 equates to 330 mana or around 10% more than you'd normally have anyway at that level (for your average caster).  That's 1/2 a blue bubble.  Nothing to stress over.  My INT currently sits at 225 because if I swap out for all my +INT gear (which only gets me to 251, grrr) I end up losing some 380 hp.  I think that the hundreds of points of +mana and +hp on the items I swap out is far more valuable to me than 156 mana with no ac and no hp at all. <p>Dalynia Aziz<br>
Arch Mage of Amici<br>
Innoruuk Server<br>
