The Final Covenant</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uenuch12.showPublicProfile?language=EN>enuch12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/25/02 5:06:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1002.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: After int, what next?</span><hr size=1> To answer the question about more skill points:<br>
<br>
Part of the point of raising the int/wis caps was to make it more difficult to maximize your mana.  When the cap is only 200, it is trivial to hit the cap.  Now that it is 250, high end gear actually does something besides give hp/resists.<br>
<br>
enuch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unoobmasterzatharas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoobmasterZatharas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/25/02 5:22:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1002.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rlinda.addr.com/deadofwinter/gallery/gun-smiley.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: After int, what next?</span><hr size=1> After your necro hits 200int or so, go FULL HP gear, HP in my opinion is the universal best stat, but it especially is for necros because in the high end game, the longer you can stay liched, the better, lich drains something like 40hp a tick, so the more HP, the long you can keep it on, that means more mana to give to enchanters and clerics, and more mana to cast group buffs. Im sorry to say but that's about what a necro does in the high end game. <p><img src="http://squirming.net/meme/tests/affliction/rickets.gif" title="I am Rickets. Hear your bones go boing."><br \><a href="http://squirming.net/meme/tests/affliction/">Take the Affliction Test Today!</a>
