</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ujeisenne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeisenne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/25/02 1:26:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1002.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.notoriouskillers.com/illusion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: After int, what next?</span><hr size=1> My int is at 233 buffed with enlightenment, but I have a ton of +mana/hp gear (more mana than hp) and a lot of +cha items since cha is important to enchanters (215 cha buffed).  I've been considering swapping out some of my +cha gear for +hp/mana gear though.<br>
<br>
I have just under 3400 mana at level 58, and just under 1500 hp self buffed (using shield of the magi), so I don't think I'm doing too shabby on the stats.  I do a lot of AE groups lately and by the time the other chanter calls out oom, usually I still have 40-60m in my mana pool and that's AFTER I buff bedlam/rune5 on the puller, mass AE stuns until the last mob is dead (using all 4 AE color stun spells we get)...<br>
<br>
I know I can probably up my HP more, but I choose to up my mana since with Ageo I sit at 2650 hp, more if I had focus and RH buffed.  Plus I usually group with clerics I know can keep me alive, so HP isn't that big of a concern to me.  Being able to keep up stuns so that the other casters can med for a final nuke or two, or so that I can toss a last minute rune, or maybe hold a few mezzes so that group members can med... that's more important to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://notoriouskillers.com/jeisenne.gif">
